Name: Brix Refractometers YR05872 // YR05884
Short description: Manufacturer: Kalstein \n \n
Description:
Brix Refractometer is frequently used by grape growers, vegetables growers, home brewers as well as food producers for Brix testing of sucrose levels in their fruit. \nBrix refers to the measurement of the percentage of sugars and dissolved solids in a given weight of fresh plant juice. These solids include sucrose, fructose, vitamins, minerals, amino acids, proteins, hormones, and other solids commonly found in a plant's juice. This RHB-05 is specially designed for cutting liquids testing. Also, it can be used to test the low brix solution. \n

Description:
The Kalstein hand-held optical refractometer measures the density of sugars in the solution and gives you an instant gravity reading at any point during the boil, or run off from the mash.   • Easy calibration: With 1 drop of water, press the "ZERO" button to return to zero. It can be operated with one hand. The special induction tank is not easy to flow out
    • \n
  • Portable and Exquisite, Low power consumption, Anti-loss design.
    • \n
  • High accurate measurement: The resolution is 0.01 and High accurate sensor. Coffee concentration (TDS) and coffee sugar (Brix value) can be measured
    • \n
  • Scientific Design: Using linear CMOS sensor with high precision and great repeatability, High-performance waterproof and anti-shock material. Low power consumption, with 10~50 °C automatic temperature compensation function, IP65 waterproof protection level.
    • \n

Name: Digital Brix+Salinity Refractometers YR05961 // YR05965
Short description: Manufacturer: Kalstein \n \n
Description:
Digital Brix+Salinity Refractometer is designed to measure the concentration of soluble solids (almost 100% sugar) in aqueous solutions of sugar content of solution such as fruit juice, syrup, puree, ade, etc. Also is used for measuring salinity of solution such as sodium chloride, sea water and refractive index of measured solution. \nThe unit features automatic temperature compensation (ATC) which make temperature corrections unnecessary between 0 to 40°C (32-104°F). It utilizes the standardized brix and salinity scale which is accurate and easy to read. The digital display is quick and easy to read brix and salinity readings. \n

  • Housing material: l ABS
    • \n
  • Waterproof: IP65
    • \n
  • Auto power off: after 3 minutes of no use
